popt4jlib.NumberPartitioning

Class ReleaseFNPTaskObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • popt4jlib.NumberPartitioning.ReleaseFNPTaskObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable, ComparableTaskObject, TaskObject, ThreadSpecificComparableTaskObject, PoolableObjectIntf

    class ReleaseFNPTaskObject
extends java.lang.Object
implements ThreadSpecificComparableTaskObject, PoolableObjectIntf
    Encapsulates the requirement for calling the release() method of the PoolableObjectIntf interface, from a specific thread (the one that created the FNPTask object that it holds, as well as the object itself). Not part of the public API.

    Title: popt4jlib

    Description: A Parallel Meta-Heuristic Optimization Library in Java

    Copyright: Copyright (c) 2014-2015

    Company:

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Ioannis T. Christou

      • newInstance

        static ReleaseFNPTaskObject newInstance(FNPTask fnptask,
                                        int tid)
        returns a managed object if space exists for the current thread, else creates a new unmanaged object. This method forms the only public interface method for getting a new object (the programmer has no control over whether the object will come from the current thread's local pool or via a call to new ReleaseFNPTaskObject(o,tid);.)
        Parameters:
        fnptask - FNPTask
        tid - int
        Returns:
        ReleaseFNPTaskObject
